838]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. I, no. 1 (February 10, 1838); ceased with vol. I, no. 39 (November 17, 1838). \"Devoted to literature, politics, science, agriculture, education, general intelligence, &c.\" Also issued on microfilm from UMI. Description based on: Vol. I, no. 1 (February 10, 1838); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 9, 2015). Latest issue consulted: Vol. I, no. 39 (November 17, 1838) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 9, 2015). Piney Woods planter"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:33.390Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2015270734/", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "liberty", "amite", "mississippi"], "number": ["2469-9268", "2015270734", "931932895", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Piney Woods planter", "Planter"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "piney woods planter and amite union literary reflector (liberty, mi. [mississippi]) 1838-1838 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 37.954773, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["amite", "newspapers", "liberty (miss.)", "united states", "mississippi", "liberty"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:52:54.074Z", "title": "Piney Woods planter and Amite union literary reflector", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2015270734/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2015270735/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1838", "dates": ["[1838 TO 1840]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. I, no. 40 (November 24, 1838); ceased in 1840. Publisher: John Tothill and Wm. F. Eisely, <January 4-February 22, 1840>. Issues for Feb. 23, 1839-<Feb. 22, 1840> also have whole numbering: no. 53-<104> Also issued on microfilm from UMI. Description based on: Vol. I, no. 40 (November 24, 1838); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 16, 2015). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 2, no. 52 (February 22, 1840) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 16, 2015)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:33.390Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2015270735/", "image_url": [], "index": 3, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "liberty", "amite", "mississippi"], "number": ["2015270735", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2470-0096", "online resource", "932276686"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Planter"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "piney woods planter (liberty, mi. [mississippi]) 1838-1840 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 37.954773, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["amite", "newspapers", "liberty (miss.)", "united states", "mississippi", "liberty"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:52:54.074Z", "title": "Piney Woods planter", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2015270735/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2015270707/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1835", "dates": ["[1835 TO 1866]"], "description": ["Weekly Began in 1835; ceased with volume XXXI, number 44 (December 22, 1866). Editors: James J. Graves, <Jan. 24, 1837-Jan. 6, 1838>; Graves & Smiley, <Jan. 20, 1838-Sept. 8, 1838>; James M. Smiley, <Sept. 29, 1838-Oct. 22, 1840>; Ham. McKnight, <May 13, 1841-Mar. 12, 1842>; Augustus W. Forsythe & Thomas M. Kincade, <Apr. 2, 1842-<Jan. 17, 1843>; Hamilton McKnight, -July 15, 1843; H. McKnight and J.F. Lowry, July 22, 1843- Publisher: Augustus W. Forsythe, <January 3, 1846-December 22, 1866>. Also issued on microfilm from UMI. Des